# AIMS Medical Application - Environment Configuration

## Required Environment Variables

### Security (CRITICAL - MUST be set in production)

# JWT/Session Secret - Generate a strong random string (min 32 chars)
# In production, this MUST be set or the application will refuse to start
SESSION_SECRET=your-super-secure-random-secret-key-min-32-characters

# Node Environment - Set to 'production' for production deployments
NODE_ENV=development

# CORS Origins - Comma-separated list of allowed origins (production only)
# Example: https://yourdomain.com,https://app.yourdomain.com
CORS_ORIGINS=

# Admin Key - Required for accessing demo/bypass endpoints in non-production
# This adds an extra layer of security even in development
ADMIN_KEY=your-admin-access-key

### Database

# PostgreSQL Database URL
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/aims_medical

### AI Services

# OpenAI API Key for AI features
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key

# Deepgram API Key for transcription (optional, falls back to OpenAI)
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=your-deepgram-api-key

### File Storage (Optional)

# Cloudinary for image/document storage
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud-name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your-api-key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your-api-secret

### Communication Services (Optional)

# SendGrid for email notifications
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.your-sendgrid-api-key

# Twilio for SMS notifications
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your-account-sid
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-auth-token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1234567890

### Payment Processing (Optional)

# Stripe for billing
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your-key
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your-key

## Development Variables

# Enable demo login buttons (NEVER enable in production)
VITE_ENABLE_LOGIN_BYPASS=true

# Demo mode - enables mock data when no database is configured
DEMO_MODE=false

## Security Checklist

Before deploying to production, ensure:

1. ✅ SESSION_SECRET is set to a strong, random value (min 32 characters)
2. ✅ NODE_ENV is set to 'production'
3. ✅ CORS_ORIGINS is set to your specific domains (not '*')
4. ✅ VITE_ENABLE_LOGIN_BYPASS is removed or set to 'false'
5. ✅ DEMO_MODE is set to 'false'
6. ✅ DATABASE_URL is set to a production database
7. ✅ All API keys are production keys, not test/development keys
8. ✅ HTTPS is enforced on your deployment platform

## Generating a Secure SESSION_SECRET

Use one of the following methods to generate a secure secret:

```bash
# Using OpenSSL
openssl rand -base64 32

# Using Node.js
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"

# Using Python
python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
```

## HIPAA Compliance Notes

This application includes HIPAA audit logging. Ensure:

1. Audit logs are retained for minimum 6 years
2. Database backups include audit log tables
3. Access to audit logs is restricted to administrators only
4. Regular review of audit logs for unauthorized access

## Database Migrations

After setting DATABASE_URL, run:

```bash
npm run db:push
npm run db:seed
```

This will create the necessary tables and seed with default users.
